summary: This is a consent to search form from the Department of Justice Office of the Inspector General, authorizing the search and seizure of computer/electronic equipment and storage media. The form is signed by a consenting individual and witnessed, but no names, specific dates, or case details are provided in the visible text.
keyFacts: A consent to search form for computer/electronic equipment was executed by the DOJ Office of the Inspector General.
The consenting individual authorized a complete search of all computer/electronic equipment at an unspecified location and the seizure of hardware, storage media, and other electronic devices.
The individual certified ownership/control of the devices and relinquished any constitutional right to privacy in the devices and stored information.
The form states the consent was given voluntarily without threats, duress, or promises.
Signatures and dates are present but are illegible or redacted in the provided text, preventing identification of individuals or the specific date.
